I'm confused, if VW doesn't use paper gaskets anymore, then why are they
STILL under each and every cylinder that comes out of Argentina, Brazil, and
good ol' Mexico where all the models are still built. Even the commercial
aircooled VW engines still carry the paper gasket, it is still in the VW
service manuals, and every gasket kit from every country of manufacture
still includes them.
just a thought
Ray
